:"The Network Extension framework allows apps to customize and extend the core networking features of iOS and OS X. Learn how to use new VPN features and NetworkExtension API to create network security solutions for education and enterprise."}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc15-717-whats-new-in-network-extension-and-vpn","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-717-Whats-New-in-Network-Extension-and-VPN"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","type":"link"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2019/714":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2019\/714","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2019\/714"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDC19.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-713-Advances-in-Networking-Part-2":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-713-Advances-in-Networking-Part-2","title":"Advances in Networking, Part 2","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Take your networking apps to the next level with advances in Bonjour, custom message framing handlers, and the latest in security. You’ll also learn how to understand your networking performance by collecting metrics, and how best to use the modern networking frameworks on Apple platforms."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-713-advances-in-networking-part-2"},"WWDC19-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC19-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-702-System-Extensions-and-DriverKit":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"One of the next steps in modernizing and improving the security and reliability of macOS is to provide a better architecture for kernel extensions and drivers.  Learn how to make this transition with System Extensions and DriverKit."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-702-system-extensions-and-driverkit","kind":"article","title":"System Extensions and DriverKit","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-702-System-Extensions-and-DriverKit"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-712-Advances-in-Networking-Part-1":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep up with new and evolving networking protocols and standards by leveraging the modern networking frameworks on all Apple platforms and following best practices for efficiency and performance. In this session, learn about Low Data Mode, Combine in URLSession, WebSocket, and improvements to network mobility."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-712-advances-in-networking-part-1","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-712-Advances-in-Networking-Part-1","kind":"article","title":"Advances in Networking, Part 1"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10096-Get-ready-for-iCloud-Private-Relay":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10096-Get-ready-for-iCloud-Private-Relay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"iCloud Private Relay is an iCloud+ service that prevents networks and servers from monitoring a person’s activity across the internet. Discover how your app can participate in this transition to a more secure and private internet: We’ll show you how to prepare your apps, servers, and networks to work with iCloud Private Relay."}],"title":"Get ready for iCloud Private Relay","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10096-get-ready-for-icloud-private-relay"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-701-Advances-in-macOS-Security":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-701-Advances-in-macOS-Security","title":"Advances in macOS Security","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We are on a journey to continuously improve macOS security, with a particular focus on preventing malware and protecting user data. Join us on the next step and learn more about what’s new in Gatekeeper—for keeping malware out of macOS—as well as new protections that help keep users’ data and activity under their control."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-701-advances-in-macos-security"}}}